FBIS3-38044 "drsov038_a_94013" FBIS-SOV-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Intelligence Chief Ends Visit to Slovakia LD2402222194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1720 GMT 24 Feb 94 LD2402222194 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] [Text] Bratislava February 24 TASS -- Russian Foreign Intelligence Chief Yevgeniy Primakov ended his visit to Slovakia on Thursday [24 February]. He expressed satisfaction with the results of his talks in Bratislava, adding that both sides reiterated their willingness to develop mutual respectful relations between Russia and Slovakia. During the visit, Primakov met with the leader of the Slovak Information Service, Vladimir Mitro, other officials to discuss ways to combat organised crime, international terrorism and illegal drug trafficking, as well as the situation in trouble spots. Asked to comment on the spy scandal involving a senior CIA official, Aldrich Ames, and his wife arrested on charges of spying for the Soviet Union and then Russia for nearly a decade, Primakov replied "no comments," adding "but when I return to Moscow..."
